    "description": "The strategy is a daily, regime gated risk on allocation that seeks to harvest persistent equity momentum in leveraged US beta while explicitly standing down during credit or duration stress. Risk appetite is determined by a bond and credit composite: average cumulative momentum over short, medium, and long horizons is computed for intermediate Treasuries, investment grade credit, and high yield credit; the portfolio is forced into a defensive posture when high yield momentum is non positive or ",
    "description_full": "The strategy is a daily, regime gated risk on allocation that seeks to harvest persistent equity momentum in leveraged US beta while explicitly standing down during credit or duration stress. Risk appetite is determined by a bond and credit composite: average cumulative momentum over short, medium, and long horizons is computed for intermediate Treasuries, investment grade credit, and high yield credit; the portfolio is forced into a defensive posture when high yield momentum is non positive or when Treasury momentum dominates both credit series, with a short persistence hold to avoid immediate flip flops. This regime filter targets environments where credit deterioration or a flight to quality historically coincides with equity drawdowns, aiming to avoid the left tail in leveraged exposures. When the regime is risk on, capital is split between two competing sleeves, SPXL and TQQQ, sized by a conviction plus persistence heuristic and volatility targeting. Each sleeve receives an edge score combining recent hit rate (fraction of up days over roughly three months) with a multi horizon momentum signal (approximately 1 to 12 months) scaled by signal to noise; weights are proportional to these edge scores and then scaled down so each sleeve targets a fixed annualized volatility budget, with any residual allocated to short term Treasuries (SHV).",
